{
  "stem": "1496.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had to go with my father to a synagogue.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My-- the home was kosher, and we really were quite observant.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Was not Hasidic, however, very observant.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Traditional, very traditional.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We all had a religious education.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Actually, there was some Hebrew schools, religious schools.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "However, to our house was come-- came a man who prepared us for the synagogue prayers, and for bar mitzvah, and so forth.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, especially in the latest year, and I'm talking about the years when we found that when Hitler came to power in Germany.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You could already feel some more anti-Semitism in Poland.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "To-- just to give you an example, when we went with boys, Jewish boys, to a park or something, we used to always go in a group, because you never knew when some non-Jewish hoodlums would attack us and try to beat us up.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this-- to this extent.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You could see some newspapers, some articles, literature being distributed anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But mainly, also, you felt during the Easter time, when some non-Jewish people, Catholics, were going out from certain churches, and depends on the priest.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "If he preached anti-Semitism, they used to come out and sometimes even break windows in Jewish homes.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were aware.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "However, as you have to realize, that before the war, there was no media like today.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We didn't have television.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Very few people had radios.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But you read in the newspapers, which was always the thing what was going on in Germany, about Hitler coming to power and the law of anti-Semitism, the Nuremberg laws, and so forth.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Then, when it came to Kristallnacht, this was very well-publicized.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Also, there was-- I don't know if you're familiar with it, but in 1938, Hitler decided to throw out all the Polish Jews from Germany.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
